<subSubSection lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="397" pageId="0" pageNumber="396" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1714,2029]" lastBlockId="1.[151,1436,151,212]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="397" pageId="0" pageNumber="396">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,261,1824,1848]" pageId="0" pageNumber="396">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: Integument hard and densely pubescent. Rostrum straight with 8–9 dorsal teeth excluding the epigastric tooth, postrostral carina distinct on its entire length (
<figureCitation box="[647,705,1860,1884]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1733,1757]" captionTargetBox="[307,1279,242,1700]" captionTargetId="figure-47@1.[306,1281,235,1709]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Trachypenaeus asper Alcock, 1905 type specimen (Courtesy ZSI, Kolkata, India)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4775814" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4775814/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="396">Fig.1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[716,753,1860,1884]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,255,1931,1955]" captionTargetBox="[287,1301,180,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[286,1301,180,1907]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. A Rostrum; B. carina on 2nd abdominal segment forming a tubercle and on third segment carina starting at 1/3rd distance (T. aspera from southeastern Arabian Sea)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4775818" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4775818/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="396">2A</figureCitation>
). Hepatic spine small but well developed and hepatic sulcus indistinct. The carina on the second abdominal segment incomplete, forms a tubercle located midway. Carina on abdominal segment 3 starting at 1/3 
<superScript attach="none" box="[415,428,1931,1945]" fontSize="6" pageId="0" pageNumber="396">rd</superScript>
, from 4 to 6 complete (
<figureCitation box="[682,740,1932,1956]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1733,1757]" captionTargetBox="[307,1279,242,1700]" captionTargetId="figure-47@1.[306,1281,235,1709]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Trachypenaeus asper Alcock, 1905 type specimen (Courtesy ZSI, Kolkata, India)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4775814" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4775814/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="396">Fig.1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[751,785,1932,1956]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,255,1931,1955]" captionTargetBox="[287,1301,180,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-19@2.[286,1301,180,1907]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. A Rostrum; B. carina on 2nd abdominal segment forming a tubercle and on third segment carina starting at 1/3rd distance (T. aspera from southeastern Arabian Sea)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4775818" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4775818/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="396">2B</figureCitation>
). Carina on 6 
<superScript attach="left" box="[930,942,1931,1945]" fontSize="6" pageId="0" pageNumber="396">th</superScript>
abdominal segment end in sharp spine (
<figureCitation box="[1374,1432,1932,1956]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1733,1757]" captionTargetBox="[307,1279,242,1700]" captionTargetId="figure-47@1.[306,1281,235,1709]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Trachypenaeus asper Alcock, 1905 type specimen (Courtesy ZSI, Kolkata, India)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4775814" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4775814/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="396">Fig.1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[151,187,1968,1992]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,255,1967,1991]" captionTargetBox="[328,1260,181,1942]" captionTargetId="figure-23@3.[327,1260,180,1943]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. A. Carina on last abdominal segment ending in spine; B. carina on telson distinct (T. aspera from southeastern Arabian Sea)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4775822" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4775822/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="396">3A</figureCitation>
). Epipodes present on first three pereiopods. The spines on the telson very short or minute not easily discerned. Fifth abdominal segment shorter than the sixth and sixth almost as long as the telson. The carina on telson distinct extending throughout its length (
<figureCitation box="[390,474,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,255,1967,1991]" captionTargetBox="[328,1260,181,1942]" captionTargetId="figure-23@3.[327,1260,180,1943]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. A. Carina on last abdominal segment ending in spine; B. carina on telson distinct (T. aspera from southeastern Arabian Sea)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4775822" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4775822/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
). The median plate on the anterior portion of the thelycum semicircular, single transverse plate on the posterior portion (
<figureCitation box="[475,538,187,212]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1733,1757]" captionTargetBox="[307,1279,242,1700]" captionTargetId="figure-47@1.[306,1281,235,1709]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Trachypenaeus asper Alcock, 1905 type specimen (Courtesy ZSI, Kolkata, India)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4775814" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4775814/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4775814" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4775814" box="[151,1159,1733,1758]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4775814/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="397" startId="1.[151,255,1733,1757]" targetBox="[307,1279,242,1700]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1159,1733,1758]" box="[151,1159,1733,1758]" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,281,1733,1757]" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Alcock, 1905" authorityName="Alcock" authorityYear="1905" box="[288,666,1733,1757]" class="Malacostraca" family="Penaeidae" genus="Trachypenaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asper">
<emphasis box="[288,515,1733,1757]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">Trachypenaeus asper</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Alcock, A." box="[522,666,1733,1757]" pageId="1" pageNumber="397" pagination="508 - 532" refId="ref1115" refString="Alcock, A. (1905) A revision of the genus Penaeus, with diagnosis of some new species and varieties. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 7, 16 (95), 508 - 532. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 03745480509443078" type="journal article" year="1905">Alcock, 1905</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
type specimen (Courtesy ZSI, Kolkata, India)
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1805,2009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,398,1805,1829]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="397" reason="1">Coloration in life.</emphasis>
Body white to pinkish with numerous red chromatophores on the carapace and abdomen. Rostrum 2/3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[185,198,1840,1854]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">rd</superScript>
reddish, white toward the tip, uropods reddish and outer border of telson red. The tergum of abdominal somites 2–5 red.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="397" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1805,2009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,329,1913,1937]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="397" reason="1">Comments.</emphasis>
The study supports the conclusion of 
<bibRefCitation author="Chan, T. Y. &amp; Cleva, R. &amp; Chu, K. H." box="[738,933,1913,1937]" pageId="1" pageNumber="397" pagination="201 - 254" refId="ref1217" refString="Chan, T. Y., Cleva, R. &amp; Chu, K. H. (2016) On the genus Trachysalambria Burkenroad, 1934 (Crustacea, Decapoda, Penaeidae), with descriptions of three new species. Zootaxa, 4150 (3), 201 - 254. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4150.3.1" type="journal article" year="2016">
Chan 
<emphasis box="[802,849,1913,1937]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">et al</emphasis>
. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
that the material examined and identified as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Alcock" baseAuthorityYear="1905" class="Malacostraca" family="Penaeidae" genus="Trachysalambria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="397" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aspera">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">T. aspera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by them is indeed the species and also reports its presence from the southwest coast of 
<collectingCountry box="[1151,1209,1949,1973]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">India</collectingCountry>
. The present material has identical 16S sequence with the Taiwanese and Indonesian material reported in 
<bibRefCitation author="Chan, T. Y. &amp; Cleva, R. &amp; Chu, K. H." box="[1042,1239,1985,2009]" pageId="1" pageNumber="397" pagination="201 - 254" refId="ref1217" refString="Chan, T. Y., Cleva, R. &amp; Chu, K. H. (2016) On the genus Trachysalambria Burkenroad, 1934 (Crustacea, Decapoda, Penaeidae), with descriptions of three new species. Zootaxa, 4150 (3), 201 - 254. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4150.3.1" type="journal article" year="2016">
Chan 
<emphasis box="[1105,1152,1985,2009]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="397">et al</emphasis>
. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
